---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Heading1 from '../components/base/Heading1.astro';
import Heading2 from '../components/base/Heading2.astro';
import Paragraph from '../components/base/Paragraph.astro';
import 'highlight.js/styles/github-dark-dimmed.css';

const llmsTxtUrl = `${Astro.site}llms.txt`;
const examplePrompt = `I want to implement B2B ordering, where customers can view placed orders of colleagues. Are there any plugins that facilitate this? Use ${llmsTxtUrl}`;
---

<Layout
  metaTitle="AI integration"
  metaDescription="Use Pinelab's experience to implement features in Vendure with your AI coding assistant"
>
  <section class="mb-24">
    <Heading1>AI integration</Heading1>

    <Paragraph>
      Generating code is easy, generating production-tested code is hard — code
      needs to run in production to mature, and that's what our plugins and
      guides are for. Even if you are not planning to use our plugins,
      integrating will still give your AI assistant better context of what is
      possible with plugins.
    </Paragraph>

    <Heading2>llms.txt</Heading2>

    <Paragraph>
      We expose an llms.txt at <code>{llmsTxtUrl}</code>
      listing every plugin, its docs and other related guides. Point your AI assistant
      at it and ask about your use case.
    </Paragraph>

    <pre
      class="rounded whitespace-pre-wrap"><code class="hljs language-bash"><span class="hljs-comment"># Example prompt</span>

{examplePrompt}</code></pre>

    <div class="mt-12"></div>
  </section>
</Layout>
